  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Patients with posterior calcaneal deformity may presented by many clinical data associated
      with retrocalcaneal bursitis which occurs due to the deformity this clinical complaining
      include pain and swelling in the back of the heel.

      Many treatment choices available of this deformity with low level of response to conservative
      treatment which includes medical treatment , physiotherapy and corticosteroids injection.
      surgical treatment in cases of HAGLUND deformity is the treatment of choice including either
      endoscopic or open surgical approach for this deformity .
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
